---
title: Japanese-Style Beef & Potato Korokke  with Tangy Slaw & Katsu Mayo
description: What are korokke? You’re in for a treat! They’re tantalizingly crispy Japanese-style croquettes filled to bursting with creamy mashed potatoes and juicy ground beef within a golden-brown panko crust. You’ll shallow-fry these homemade croquettes to crunchy perfection, and serve with tangy cabbage slaw and salty-sweet katsu mayonnaise for dipping.

